fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.mapping

Interface ManyReferenceMergedAs<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - the type of the multi-valued reference after mapping
    All Superinterfaces:
    ManyReferenceMapper, ReferenceMapper, ValueMapper

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public interface ManyReferenceMergedAs<M>
extends ValueMapper, ManyReferenceMapper
    A ManyReferenceMapper that provides a default behavior to use M instead of a set of Id for multi-valued references.

    This mapper merges the multi-valued references into a single value.
